{
  "texts": [
    "The v10 assembly is also far more contiguous, with half of the sequence contained in 32 contigs longer than 14.6 Mb (in comparison, this N50-length was.",
    "71.0 kilobases [kb] in v9).",
    "The assembly captures 99.6% of known coding sequences (Supplementary Table 2 and Supplementary Note 2).",
    "We found that the fragmented quality of earlier assemblies was due, in part, to the fact that 68.3 Mb (4.71%) of the genome was not sampled by the 8× redundant Sanger dideoxy whole-genome shotgun dataset 45 (Supplementary Fig. 2a-c and Supplementary Note 2).",
    "These missing sequences are apparently due to non-uniformities in shotgun cloning and/or sequencing (Supplementary Fig. 2d-f)."
  ]
}